the year is 1997.
you’re on summer break.
parents are at work and it’s the first year they’ve let you stay home alone and not go to the community center childcare 

you ride your skateboard 2 miles over to vince’s house.
turn on MTV and find out prodigy just put out ‘the fat of the land’.

you skateboard 4 miles to the Northtown mall to pick up the CD at Best Buy.
you stop at Mrs. Fields and split a chocolate chip cookie with the money you have left over.
you look at the other end of the food court and see that someone abandoned a half filled Icee on the table. one shoulder shrug later and you each go grab new straws and finish the job.

on the way back home you try to kick flip off of the 6 stair at St William Church. 
eight tries until they kick you out. 
on try six you fall and open a wound on your knee that you don’t know is going to still be there when you’re in your mid-30’s.

finally you arrive at home and put in the CD.
you have no idea how they’re making the sounds. the next time you pick up your guitar, you turn on a fuzz and a wah pedal….bingo

*searching for a memory, to inspire a writing session

The Power Station Tour 
East Coast Live Album
now out on the streaming platforms and whatnot….

I'm a live guy. I'm not afraid to say that my band brings the HEAT and the energy in the live setting. It's where we thrive. There's nothing that can replace actually being at the live shows; but a live album allows us to capture the sound of the band at that exact moment and helps to be able to re-live that moment. It’s also a great way to mark the representation of where a band is at a specific point in their career. 
I couldn't be more thrilled with the way my band is sounding right now. This tour was incredible because I got to have one of my childhood heroes, Victor Wooten out on tour with us playing bass. Victor has been one of my favorite musicians in the world since I was a teenager, and playing with him really helped elevate our game to a new level. Trousdale is a band that I just got hip to last year after searching around for great harmony groups on the internet. They are such an amazing band and it was great to have them out with us on this last tour. Every night I watched them from side-stage win over every crowd with their incredible writing and musicianship. It was a thrill to bring them up on stage with me each night to sing a few songs as well. They're a band that I'm a forever fan of, and it's so great to have them a part of this live album!
